Note: - Observe each result from /boot/grub/grub.conf, then restart computer and try each situation.
     - Looking for related partition
        Type console
        # fdisk -l
     - Looking for kernel and initramfs
        Type console
        ls /boot/

1) Add a new bootable system
    1.a) For all system options try to left empty the textbox(es) and then observe that they give a warning about it.
    1.b) For Windows give a title and write the partition of related windows system and then click "ok".
            Observe the results with using the above note.
    1.c) Xen or Linux
        - Give a title
        - Write the partition of related system.
        - Write the kernel of related system.
        - Write the ramdisk file (initramfs) of related system.
        - Write some related boot option.
        - Then click "ok".
        - Observe the results with using the above note.
    1.d) For memtest give a title then click ok.
          Observe the results with using the above note.

2) Try to change timeout and then observe it with using the above note.
